.TH "NAVIGATIONHISTORYENTRY.GETSTATE" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
NavigationHistoryEntry.getState \- NavigationHistoryEntry: getState()
method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]getState()\f[B]\f[R] method of the
\f[CR]NavigationHistoryEntry\f[R] interface returns a clone of the
developer\-supplied state associated with this history entry.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
getState()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
A value representing the state.
This can be any structured\-cloneable data type.
.PP
If no state is defined or if current document is not fully active, it
returns \f[CR]undefined\f[R].
.SS Exceptions
None.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[B]async\f[R] \f[B]function\f[R] handleReload() {
  \f[I]// Update existing state via reload()\f[R]
  \f[B]await\f[R] navigation.reload({
    state: { ...navigation.currentEntry.getState(), newState: 3 },
  });

  \f[I]// Print current state to the console\f[R]
  \f[B]const\f[R] current = navigation.currentEntry;
  console.log(current.getState());
}
.EE
